A simple HTML page with a bit of javascript that loads whatever Graphite graph you give it in size of the current window, and then auto-refreshes every ten seconds.

Usage:

http://andrewseward.github.io/GraphiteView?g= <the url of your Graphite graph image>

e.g. http://andrewseward.github.io/GraphiteView?g=http://mygraphiteinstance.com/render/?width=1610&height=937&_salt=1392913357.74&from=-6weeks&target=alias(summarize(sumSeries(graphite.metric.*.count)%2C%221d%22)%2C%22Per%20Day%22)&title=Total%20Processed

